    <section id="oversharing" class="mt-10 scroll-mt-24">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold">Oversharing traps (common in small towns)</h2>
      <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
        <li><strong>Routine posts</strong>: “Every Friday at…” can reveal patterns.</li>
        <li><strong>School + sport + schedule</strong>: kids’ safety can depend on limiting public details.</li>
        <li><strong>Local groups</strong>: neighborhood pages often expose addresses and family relationships.</li>
        <li><strong>Photos</strong>: street signs, house numbers, work badges, and license plates are “free OSINT.”</li>
      </ul>
